OL,3,CControversial plans to house asylum
OL,4,Cseekers in derelict prison, scrapped
OL,6,FControversial plans by the previous
OL,7,Fgovernment to use a derelict prison to
OL,8,Fhouse asylum seekers have been
OL,9,Fscrapped.
OL,11,FThe former government bought the
OL,12,FNortheye site in Bexhill-on-Sea,
OL,13,FSussex last year, after promises to
OL,14,Fstop housing migrants in hotels.
OL,16,FRobert Jenrick, former immigration
OL,17,Fminister, announced on March 29 2023
OL,18,Fthat his government would develop the
OL,19,FNortheye site to house 1,200 migrants.
OL,20,FThe purchase was then completed in
OL,21,FSeptember 2023.
