OL,6,FThe National Audit Office (NAO),
OL,7,FWhitehall's spending watchdog,
OL,8,Fcriticised the move, saying the Home
OL,9,FOffice paid more than double the price
OL,10,Ffor the site had been bought for in
OL,11,F2022 - around #6.3 million.
OL,13,FLabour ministers said progressing with
OL,14,Fthe plans would have taken
OL,15,F"significant time" and incurred
OL,16,Fadditional "costs". The Home Office
OL,17,Fnow hopes to sell the land.
