OL,3,CControversial plans to house asylum
OL,4,Cseekers in derelict prison, scrapped
OL,6,FCllr Doug Oliver, leader of Rother
OL,7,FDistrict Council said: "After almost
OL,8,Ftwo years of uncertainty and
OL,9,Funanswered questions, we welcome the
OL,10,Fdecision by the new Government not to
OL,11,Fpush ahead with plans to use the
OL,12,Fformer Northeye prison site in Bexhill
OL,13,Fto house asylum seekers.
OL,15,F"Apart from serious questions about
OL,16,Fthe safety of the site and its
OL,17,Fbuildings, we shared residents'
OL,18,Fconcerns about the impact such a plan
OL,19,Fwould have on the community and local
OL,20,Fservices, particularly those living
OL,21,Fnear the site.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/6
